sentences: Garnett Brown (January 31, 1936 â€“ October 9, 2021) was a jazz trombonist who worked with The Crusaders, Herbie Hancock, Lionel Hampton, Earth Wind and Fire and others.
In 1989 he was the conductor and orchestrator for Harlem Nights.
Coincident with Kenny Burrell joining UCLA as Director of Jazz Studies in 1996, Brown co-led UCLA Jazz Ensemble I with John Clayton.
